        <Paragraph></Paragraph>
        <Paragraph> "<i>For <Bold>ye are all the children of God</Bold> by faith in Christ Jesus</i>." ( Gal 3: 26 )</Paragraph>
        <Paragraph></Paragraph>
        <Paragraph> "<Bold>And because ye are sons</Bold><i>, God hath sent forth the Spirit of his Son into your hearts,
            crying,
            Abba, Father</i>." ( Gal 4: 6 )</Paragraph>
        <Paragraph></Paragraph>
        <Paragraph> "<i>That ye may be blameless and harmless, <Bold>the sons of God</Bold>, without rebuke, in the midst of
            a
            crooked and perverse nation, among whom ye shine as lights in the world</i>." ( Phil 2: 15 )</Paragraph>
        <Paragraph><Bold>After considering all these biblical arguments, let's now use our common sense. <i>Neither demons,
            nor any
            creature can create anything</i></Bold>. A demon cannot create a human body, <Bold>give life to each
            cell</Bold>, produce genital organs, make spermatozoids with chromosomes, genes, DNA, etc., to later
            introduce
            himself in that body, and have children with a woman, as said by the Russellists. This simply is not true.
        </Paragraph>
        <Paragraph> Russellists also claim that according to Gn 6: 4, the sexual participation of demons, began the existence of
            giants
            on the Earth. <Bold>This again is false. Otherwise all the children of demon-possessed men would be
                giants,
                something we know is not true.</Bold></Paragraph>
        <Paragraph> Russellists have not noticed that in this very verse it says that <Bold>the giants existed before</Bold>
            the
            sons of God married the daughters of men, and also after it.</Paragraph>
        <Paragraph> "<Bold>There were giants in the earth in those days</Bold><i>; <Bold>and also after that, when the
            sons of God
            came in unto the daughters of men</Bold>, and they bare children to them, the same became mighty men which
            were of
            old, men of renown</i>." ( Gn 6: 4 )</Paragraph>
        <Paragraph> As we know, during the Creation, God created <Bold>only one man, Adam</Bold>. According to the
            Russellists, God
            restarted His work with a second creation, <Bold>but this time, instead of creating one man, He created
                thousands
                of them, and to boot, God created them with better genes than Adam, because their offspring were
                giants</Bold>.
            Absurd!!</Paragraph>
        <Paragraph> Something else to realize is that if these supposed demons, incarnated along a long period of time, then it
            have to
            be concluded that God worked for years or decades creating bodies for these abominable beings, instead of
            working
            only one day as when He created Adam. Absurd.</Paragraph>
        <Paragraph><Bold>Let's see another absurd claimed by Russellists. They insist that there is no soul, but only flesh.
            According
            to that, feelings, character and personality are just in the brain and not in the soul</Bold>. If this was
            so,
            then they would have to admit the following: <Bold>a)</Bold> These newly created bodies, which were
            fashioned
            especially for demons, <Bold>had a brain</Bold>. In which case they were regular men, with their own
            individuality, feelings, and human personality, created by God, with the only purpose of being possessed by
            a demon.
            This is a blaspheme against God. <Bold>b)</Bold> The other alternative is that, to preclude those bodies
            from
            having a human personality, <Bold>they were created without brains</Bold>. In this case they have to
            believe the
            bizarre idea of a human body that performs perfectly well without a brain.</Paragraph>
        <Paragraph><Bold>In short, to think that this teaching is true means one of two: 1)</Bold> either rebellious angels
            have a
            power and a wisdom equal to God, or <Bold>2)</Bold> God agreed with these demons in creating a body for
            them for
            the sole purpose of committing this horrid sin. Both ideas equally absurd and blasphemous.</Paragraph>
        <Paragraph> This idea of "materialization" of angels must be related to the materialization of the spirits, as seen in
            the
            believers of spiritualism.</Paragraph>
